{EAST's 4\C is a Splinter bid. 
He promises 13+ points, at least four \Hs and a singleton or void in \Cs.

WEST is obviously forced to game, but she is not thrilled to hear about EAST's \C shortness. In fact, 
it does nothing to help the value of her hand. So she bids the \H game.}

